If we assume Gaussian statistics for the errors, we end up with a standard least squares formulation with covariance matrix given by the sum of the measurement and solution error covariance matrices [25]. For this case, the misÔ¨Åt (which in this paper always refers to the negative log of the likelihood) is given by

